# CursorRules for Carpe Tree'em Project
project_name: Carpe Tree'em
description: Tree service management platform with AI-driven tree identification, customer CRM, and service automation.

tech_stack:
  frontend:
    - React.js
    - Tailwind CSS
    - HTML5 / CSS3 / JavaScript
    - Axios (for HTTP requests)
  backend:
    - Node.js with Express
    - Python (for AI tree identification and data processing)
    - Multer (for file uploads)
    - JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for authentication
   database:
    - MySQL (managed through Hostinger)(primary database for customer data and service records)
  integrations:
    - n8n (for workflow automation)
    - Twilio (SMS notifications)
    - SendGrid (email notifications)
    - AWS S3 (media storage)
  AI and Machine Learning:
    - TensorFlow (AI tree species identification)
    - OpenAI (language model support)
  security:
    - HTTPS (secure web communication)
    - Data encryption for sensitive data storage
    - GDPR compliance for customer data handling

rules:
  - Ensure consistent use of Primary Green `#4A7C59` for UI elements.
  - All icons must be flat-style and SVG format for scalability.
  - Use ESLint for code linting and Prettier for formatting.
  - Document all API endpoints in OpenAPI format (Swagger).
  